Hi @chece1969, can you please go to your Firebase console and post the first couple of keys of items at "test/people"? 

The reason being we need to check if Firebase itself (not Pyrebase) is returning a list instead if a dictionary.

For example if we have the following data at "test/people" we should get the response you are expecting:

'''
jsheif2472: {
  name: "john"
},
kfn46jsbi84: {
  name: "henry"
}
''' 

However if our keys are a sequence of numbers like this:
'''
0: {
  name: "john"
},
1: {
  name: "henry"
}
''' 
...then Firebase will actually just return a list that includes no keys, for example:

'''
[{name:"john"}, {name: "henry"}]
'''
And in this case Pyrebase can't actually get the proper keys because they were never sent.

If you could help me with that extra info that would be really great, thanks.

