Kinematic bodies are allowed to have `CF_STATIC_OBJECT` set right?
If so, the kinematic conditional will never be reached. To clarify, getOrInitSolverBody contains the following structure:

```
if (!body.isStaticOrKinematicObject()) {
    // dynamic body.
}
else if (body.isStaticObject())
{
    // static body.
}
else
{
    // kinematic body.
}
```

Suggest reordering so that we check for kinematic body before static body:

```
if (!body.isStaticOrKinematicObject()) {
    // dynamic body.
}
else if (body.isKinematicObject())
{
    // kinematic body.
}
else
{
    // static body.
}
```

